# UDS Figma Change Classification

Any change derived from Figma MUST be classified before an agent edits the
doc site or writes back to Figma.

## Required finding shape

Every Figma-derived finding must include:

```markdown
Confidence: high | medium | low
Risk: non-breaking | potentially-breaking | destructive | unknown
Reason: <why this confidence/risk was chosen>
Default action: auto-apply | report-only | ask-user | stop
```

## Confidence levels

### High confidence

All of these are true:

- Exact Figma file and version were preflighted.
- The relevant collection/page/node was read directly, not inferred from a
  screenshot.
- Stable IDs or exact normalized names match the doc-site artifact.
- No ambiguity exists between multiple possible nodes/tokens.
- Current Figma data, current doc-site files, and the last sync snapshot agree
  about identity.

### Medium confidence

One of these is true:

- A single likely match exists, but names differ.
- Stable IDs are unavailable, but normalized names and structure match.
- Optional metadata is missing, but the core object is unambiguous.
- A rename/move candidate exists with strong but not exact evidence.

### Low confidence

Any of these are true:

- Multiple possible Figma nodes/tokens could match.
- Evidence comes primarily from screenshots.
- Required Figma structure is missing or partially unreadable.
- Modes, aliases, or variant properties are incomplete.
- A change conflicts with current CSS/spec behavior.

## Risk classes

### Non-breaking

May auto-apply only when confidence is high:

- Token value changed but token name and mode remain stable.
- New token added.
- New optional component prop/state/slot added.
- `figmaNodeId` added for an unambiguous component.
- Component status moves forward, e.g. `in-progress` -> `review`.

### Potentially breaking

Never auto-apply:

- Token removed, renamed, or moved to a different generated CSS name.
- Mode removed or renamed.
- CSS custom property name would change.
- Semantic alias target removed.
- Required component prop renamed or removed.
- Component variant/property removed.
- Component status moves backward from `review` or `production`.

### Destructive

Always stop and ask:

- Component removed from Figma.
- Component split or merge.
- Figma write outside an explicitly allowed write scope.
- Doc-site page deletion, sidebar removal, or CSS token deletion.

## Auto-apply policy

| Finding | Default action |
|---|---|
| high confidence + non-breaking | auto-apply allowed |
| medium confidence | ask user |
| low confidence | stop and ask user |
| potentially breaking | stop and ask user |
| destructive | stop and ask user |
| unknown risk | stop and ask user |

## Dry-run behavior

The `uds-updated` skill MUST support dry-run mode. In dry-run mode:

- Read Figma and repo files.
- Classify changes.
- Report proposed actions.
- Do not edit files.
- Do not write Figma.
- Do not update sync snapshots.
- Do not commit or push.
